physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Multiple cutaneous neurofibromas and axillary freckling; atrophy of the left supraspinatus and infraspinatus; active forward elevation of 100° and passive forward elevation of 110°; active external and internal rotation was 50% of the contralateral side; positive lift-off test; persistent sensory deficit in axillary nerve with no motor impairment.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: No substantial change noted at five years after the initial presentation.
